  "notes": "LGN is a gated thalamic relay nucleus. Relay cells transmit retinal input to primary visual cortex (V1). Activity is modulated by top-down cortical feedback from PFC and inhibited by TRN-mediated thalamic gating. Relay gating behavior is enforced at runtime, not structurally here."
